---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="WorldCup App · Built 100% with AI" description="A football prediction app built entirely with AI tools, from spec to deployed product.">
  <div class="bg-slate-950 min-h-screen">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-32 pb-24">

    <a href="/projects" class="text-sm text-slate-500 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8 inline-block">← All projects</a>

    <div class="mb-2">
      <span class="text-xs font-medium text-emerald-400 bg-emerald-950/50 rounded px-2.5 py-1">Live</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-2">WorldCup App</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 mb-10">A football prediction app built entirely with AI.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-indigo-500 bg-slate-900/60 p-6">
        <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium">
          "What does AI-first development actually look like, end to end? I built this to find out."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">The context</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          A team initiative to run a World Cup office pool was about to be managed through a shared Excel. Manual scoring, no real-time updates, low engagement. I decided to build the real thing instead: a full web app, in less than a week, using AI throughout.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">What I built</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">End-to-end web application replacing the spreadsheet approach entirely.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {[
            "Match prediction system for all participants",
            "Real-time leaderboard with automated scoring",
            "Live visibility of other users' predictions",
            "Social layer with chat between participants",
            "Admin panel for result management and system updates",
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-slate-400">
              <span class="text-indigo-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▸</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">The AI-first approach</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Design, code, testing, deployment: AI tools were the primary instrument throughout. From spec to shipped in under a week. Not a prototype, a working product used by a real team.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">What I learned</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          {[
            "AI compresses timelines drastically on boilerplate, but the hard parts remain hard",
            "Prompt quality matters more than model choice when the logic gets complex",
            "Debugging AI-generated code requires genuine understanding, not just running it",
            "You ship faster, but you also ship bugs faster. Testing discipline is non-negotiable.",
            "A simple need, turned into a product, creates engagement that a spreadsheet never could",
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-slate-400">
              <span class="text-slate-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0">·</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-slate-800 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {["Full-stack", "React", "AI-built", "Experiment", "Claude"].map(tag => (
        <span class="text-xs text-blue-400 bg-blue-950/40 rounded px-2 py-0.5">{tag}</span>
      ))}
    </div>

  </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
